The paper discusses a methodology for writing strong specifications and evaluates its cost and benefits in the context of testing data structure implementations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The methodology extends Design by Contract, which is a programming language feature commonly associated with Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions invariants, which are a concept from Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The evaluation involves detecting bugs, which is a topic in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and System and Control (cs.SY).
